com.mapbox.api.directions.v5

Class MapboxDirections

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mapbox.core.MapboxService<DirectionsResponse>
      • com.mapbox.api.directions.v5.MapboxDirections

  • public abstract class MapboxDirections
extends com.mapbox.core.MapboxService<DirectionsResponse>
    The Directions API allows the calculation of routes between coordinates. The fastest route can be returned with geometries, turn-by-turn instructions, and much more. The Mapbox Directions API supports routing for driving cars (including live traffic), riding bicycles and walking. Requested routes can include as much as 25 coordinates anywhere on earth (except the traffic profile).

    Requesting a route at a bare minimal must include, a Mapbox access token, destination, and an origin.

    Since:
    1.0.0
    See Also:
    Android Directions documentation, Directions API documentation
